## Slides

* Which image is more blurry #1
    - Use an image that's out of focus paired with an image that's in focus
        * https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/59/Focus_stacking_Tachinid_fly.jpg
    - After poll, ask students what the cause of the blur is (don't provide the answer in the slides)
* Which image is more blurry #2
    - Use an image with clear motion blur paired with an image without
        * https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d3c3d8a01c19f00011603bc/e73031e4-94de-4eef-bc96-75a3fb096962/Motion+Blur+thumbnail+%E2%80%93+1.jpg
    - After poll, ask students what the cause of the blur is (don't provide the answer in the slides)
* Which image is more blurry #3
    - Remove it
* What does blurry mean slide
    - In the first box, use the image at this link: https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/685be7dcd32275d383065239/685be7dcd32275d3830681f5_Blog%20Cover_%202024_03_%20How%20to%20Blur%20Your%20Zoom%20Background%20Before%20_%20During%20Your%20Meetings.webp

* Remove the "/ N" after the filter grid visualizations. No need to clarify how these filters are normalized.


